# UI Consistency Standards

## Color System

Semantic ramps are configured in [`core/templates/core/base.html`](core/templates/core/base.html) (`tailwind.config`): `primary-*`, `success-*`, `warning-*`, `danger-*`, `info-*`, `muted-*`.

| Use | Class |
|-----|-------|
| Primary buttons | `bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white` |
| Secondary buttons | `bg-white border border-gray-300 text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50` |
| Danger buttons | `bg-danger-600 hover:bg-danger-700 text-white` (or legacy `bg-red-*`) |
| Success indicators | `text-success-600`, `bg-success-50`, borders `border-success-*` |
| Warning indicators | `text-warning-600`, `bg-warning-50` |
| Error indicators | `text-danger-600`, `bg-danger-50` |
| Active nav link | `text-primary-700 bg-primary-100` (`.nav-link.active`) |

Prefer these tokens over literal hex classes in templates.

## Reusable Components (`templates/components/`)

All are included with context variables; primitives live under `templates/components/` except `modal.html`.

| Include | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `{% include "components/page_header.html" with title="..." subtitle="..." icon="fa-..." %}` | Title row; optional `back_url`, `breadcrumbs`, `actions` |
| `{% load app_subnav %}{% appointments_subnav %}` (per app tag) | App section nav — tags live in [`core/templatetags/app_subnav.py`](core/templatetags/app_subnav.py); each app `_subnav.html` loads the tag |
| `{% include "components/sub_nav.html" with items=items %}` | Built-in primitive (used internally by inclusion tags) |
| `{% include "components/empty_state.html" with icon="..." title="..." ... %}` | Empty lists |
| `{% include "components/status_badge.html" with label="..." variant="success\|warning\|danger\|info\|primary\|muted" %}` | Status pills |
| `{% include "components/stat_card.html" with ... %}` | Dashboard counters |
| `{% include "components/card.html" with title="..." %}` | Wrapped content |
| `{% include "components/data_table.html" with ... %}` | Table shells |
| `{% include "components/pagination.html" with ... %}` | Paginator controls |
| `{% include "components/breadcrumbs.html" with crumbs=breadcrumbs %}` | Trail |
| `{% include "components/avatar.html" with ... %}` | Initials avatar |
| `{% include "components/tab_bar.html" with items=... %}` | Tab strip |
| `{% include "components/button.html" with ... %}` | Styled button/link |
| `{% include "components/forms/field.html" with ... %}` | Unified field renderer |
| `{% include "components/forms/section.html" with ... %}` | Section header + grid |
| `{% include "components/forms/submit_bar.html" with ... %}` | Sticky actions |
| `{% include "components/layouts/page_list.html" %}` (+ blocks) | List layout |
| `{% include "components/layouts/page_detail.html" %}` (+ blocks) | Detail layout |
| `{% include "components/layouts/page_form.html" %}` (+ blocks) | Form layout |

Layouts extend `core/base.html` and expose blocks (`page_header`, `list`, …).

## Alpine Modal (`components/modal.html`)

Include once via `core/base.html`. Open from anywhere:

```html
<button type="button" @click="$dispatch('open-modal', {
  type: 'danger',
  title: 'Delete',
  message: 'This cannot be undone.',
  actionLabel: 'Delete',
})">Delete</button>
```

- **Embedded form body**: put markup in a hidden container, then dispatch with `embedFrom: '#hidden-id'` and `hasForm: true` (used for health-form review/delete). The global `modalComponent` copies inner HTML server-side markup into the modal (`core/base.html`).
- **Confirm callback**: optional `onConfirm` in `$dispatch('open-modal', { ... })`.

Never use inline `display:none` + `onclick` pattern modals for new UI.

## Toasts & Messages

- Server: Django `messages` + [`templates/partials/messages.html`](templates/partials/messages.html) bridges to Alpine `user-toast` (`$dispatch('user-toast', …)` on init).
- HTMX: [`core/htmx_utils.htmx_add_toast`](core/htmx_utils.py).
- Avoid ad-hoc `showToast()` JavaScript in templates.

## Icons

Font Awesome **6** `<i class="fas fa-*">` for UI icons.

## Forms

Shared widget classes (`.form-input`, `.form-select`, `.form-textarea`, `.has-error`, …) are defined in [`static/css/form-elements.css`](static/css/form-elements.css); health form bases no longer duplicate inline `<style>` blocks.

## Sub-navigation Convention

Every app exposes `…/_subnav.html` that does `{% load app_subnav %}` and calls one inclusion tag (`appointments_subnav`, `analytics_subnav`, …). Messaging adds a short “Communication” label above its nav strip.

